Windows User (GUI interaction) mode and Kernel mode (OS technology, services)
User mode: application starts a process (private virtual adress space, private hande rable) Each app runs in issolation.
Kernel mode: all code from kernel rus in single virtual address space. If driver writes data to wrong place, kernel or other driver data will be compromised.
If cernel mode driver crashes, the OS crashes too.

File systems (enables application to store and retrieve files on storage devices. Files are placed in hierarchical structure. Naming conventions. 
File is unit of data in file system
Directory is a hirarchical collection of directorues and files.
NTFS and FAT
-NTFS (new technology file system) 1993
-FATxx (file allocation table) since 80's. Number tells block size in bits. FAT16, FAT32. Used mainly for remote storage devices under 32GB capacity.

Directory structure:
Different bit systems different amount of memory that can be addressed for apps.
Programs - progam files
ProgramData - every users programs data location
User dir - for user profile
App Data - program data specific to user
Windows - windows system directory (System, System32, SysWow64(32-bit DLLs)for DLL files)


